      "id": "PopularPost176170",
      "post_content": "I'd say errata these and others eligible to bovines. Bovines are IIRC the only gender divided type in MtG. [Arc Runner](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arc Runner), [Ironhoof Ox](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ironhoof Ox), [Longhorn Firebeast](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Longhorn Firebeast), [Pillarfield Ox](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pillarfield Ox), [Raging Bull](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Raging Bull), [Wild Ox](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wild Ox) and [Zodiac Ox](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Zodiac Ox) are all type ox wheras [Hungry Hungry Heifer](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hungry Hungry Heifer) and [Krazy Kow](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Krazy Kow) are type cow.  \n  \nTo change all these to bovines would stop the sexism and the error that all those oxen are actuall bulls.",
      "posted_by": "tavaritz",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost176170\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_post\">I'd say errata these and others eligible to bovines. Bovines are IIRC the only gender divided type in MtG. <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Arc Runner\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arc Runner\">Arc Runner</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ironhoof Ox\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ironhoof Ox\">Ironhoof Ox</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Longhorn Firebeast\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Longhorn Firebeast\">Longhorn Firebeast</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Pillarfield Ox\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pillarfield Ox\">Pillarfield Ox</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Raging Bull\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Raging Bull\">Raging Bull</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Wild Ox\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wild Ox\">Wild Ox</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Zodiac Ox\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Zodiac Ox\">Zodiac Ox</a> are all type ox wheras <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Hungry Hungry Heifer\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hungry Hungry Heifer\">Hungry Hungry Heifer</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Krazy Kow\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Krazy Kow\">Krazy Kow</a> are type cow.<br/><br/>To change all these to bovines would stop the sexism and the error that all those oxen are actuall bulls.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"Hand